        Forschungsumgebung / beta maṣāḥǝft Felber Brill,  IslHornAfr: Islam in the Horn of Africa, A Comparative Literary Approach. European Research Council (Advanced Grant no. 322849)</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>PRS0061IHA</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">ar</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Gori</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>P. Bearman, Th. Bianquis, C.E. Bosworth, E. van Donzel, W.P. Heinrichs</dc:contributor><foaf:gender>male</foaf:gender><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ontology/pers"/><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">الجويني, ابو المعالي عبد الملك بن ابي محمد عبد الله بن يوسف</foaf:name><foaf:name>al-Ǧuwaynī, Abū al-Maʻālī ʻAbd al-Malik b. Abī Muḥammad ʻAbd Allāh b. Yūsuf</foaf:name><foaf:name>
                  Imām al-Ḥaramayn
               </foaf:name><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E67_Birth"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0419-01-18 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E67_Birth"/><crm:P79_beginning_is_qualified_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1028-02-17</crm:P79_beginning_is_qualified_by><crm:P80_end_is_qualified_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1028-02-17</crm:P80_end_is_qualified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E69_Death"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0478-04-25 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E69_Death"/><crm:P79_beginning_is_qualified_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1085-08-20</crm:P79_beginning_is_qualified_by><crm:P80_end_is_qualified_by rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">1085-08-20</crm:P80_end_is_qualified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><crm:P78_is_identified_by>5th / 9th century (d. 478 / 1085)He was connected with the school of ʿilm al-kalām inaugurated by Abū al-Ḥasan al-Ašʿarī at the beginning of the 4th/10th century. But ʿAmīd al-Mulk al-Kundurī, vizier of the Salǧūq Tuġrul Beg, declared himself against this “innovation”, and had the Ašʿarīs, as well as the Rawāfiḍ, denounced from the pulpits. Al-Ǧuwaynī, like Abū al-Qāsim al-Qušayrī, immediately left his country and went to Baġdād; then, in 450/1058, he reached the Ḥiǧāz where he taught at Mecca and at Medina for four years: hence his honorary name of “Imām of the two holy Cities”. But when the vizier Niẓām al-Mulk came to power in the Salǧūq empire, he favoured the Ašʿarīs and invited the emigrants to return home.
               </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span></rdf:Description><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0061IHA/person/annotation/1"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0061IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0051IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>الغزالي ابو حميد محمد بن محمد الطوسي</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation></rdf:RDF>